till they get to Miami.

27
00:08:56,095 --> 00:08:58,325
<i>However, everything looks
so different today.</i>

28
00:08:59,474 --> 00:09:01,783
<i>Have I changed, or has the city?</i>

29
00:09:29,764 --> 00:09:32,039
<i>The moment of parting.</i>

30
00:09:33,477 --> 00:09:36,674
<i>"Oh, abandoned, like the
wharves at dawn.</i>

31
00:09:37,023 --> 00:09:39,412
<i>"Everything about you
was like a shipwreck."</i>

32
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:53,066
<i>- What are you doing?
- Can't you see?</i>

33
00:09:54,713 --> 00:09:56,749
<i>What are you reading?</i>

34
00:09:57,550 --> 00:10:02,863
<i>Something trite, frivolous and
superficial. "The Best of Everything."</i>

35
00:10:03,475 --> 00:10:05,511
<i>Oh, yes, that film...</i>

36
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,503
<i>Stop looking at me...</i>

37
00:10:11,819 --> 00:10:14,014
<i>...as if I'm some strange insect!</i>

38
00:10:16,241 --> 00:10:17,640
<i>Letùs talk.</i>

39
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:20,424
<i>Whaùs biting you?</i>

40
00:10:21,206 --> 00:10:24,164
<i>You only talk about insects lately.</i>

41
00:10:24,502 --> 00:10:25,935
<i>Why not?</i>

42
00:10:26,338 --> 00:10:31,776
<i>Aren't we surrounded by insects?
Isn't this country falling behind?</i>

43
00:10:32,346 --> 00:10:35,099
<i>I say so, but what do you think?</i>

44
00:10:35,475 --> 00:10:39,434
<i>Why? You've never been interested
in my opinions.</i>

45
00:10:41,191 --> 00:10:45,548
<i>You're practising your English
lately. I think you want to leave.</i>

46
00:10:45,989 --> 00:10:48,105
<i>Clear off! Leave me alone!</i>

47
00:10:48,409 --> 00:10:52,004
<i>I like you when you become vulgar.</i>

48
00:10:52,497 --> 00:10:54,852
<i>It always excites me...</i>

49
00:10:56,377 --> 00:10:59,972
<i>... when I see you struggle between
elegance and vulgarity.</i>

50
00:11:03,512 --> 00:11:06,822
<i>I've been keeping an eye on you
for some time now.</i>

51
00:11:08,727 --> 00:11:11,525
<i>You've become rather disgusting
lately.</i>

52
00:11:12,148 --> 00:11:14,582
<i>Because I've run out of
Yardley's brilliantine...</i>

53
00:11:14,985 --> 00:11:19,456
<i>...and Colgate toothpaste
and after-shave lotion.</i>

54
00:11:20,492 --> 00:11:22,608
<i>Those things help a lot,
don't they?</i>

55
00:11:24,998 --> 00:11:27,193
<i>Yet you become more attractive
every day.</i>

56
00:11:28,294 --> 00:11:30,683
<i>You're more artificial.</i>

57
00:11:31,173 --> 00:11:34,051
<i>I prefer women like you
to natural beauty.</i>

58
00:11:34,385 --> 00:11:39,823
<i>I prefer good clothes, good food,
make-up, massage.</i>

59
00:11:41,019 --> 00:11:45,297
<i>Thanks to such things you're
no longer a slovenly Cuban girl.</i>

60
00:11:46,193 --> 00:11:49,947
<i>I never know whether you're
serious or joking.</i>

61
00:11:50,448 --> 00:11:51,517
<i>A little of both.</i>

62
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:54,062
<i>Go joke to your mother!</i>

63
00:11:58,709 --> 00:12:03,942
<i>I can't stand living here
any longer! You stink!</i>

64
00:12:11,225 --> 00:12:13,375
<i>Everything you said was recorded.</i>

65
00:12:15,147 --> 00:12:18,935
<i>Every word. I'ùll be fun when
you hear it played back.</i>

66
00:12:19,403 --> 00:12:22,713
<i>You monster! I'll smash
the recorder!</i>

67
00:13:55,529 --> 00:13:59,920
<i>Women look into your eyes as though
wishing to be touched by your look.</i>

68
00:14:07,085 --> 00:14:10,555
<i>Such a thing only happens here.</i>

69
00:14:13,636 --> 00:14:17,709
<i>Maybe Italian women stare longer,
but no, not like ours.</i>

70
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:46,116
<i>Havana's like a country town
since "El Encanto" burned down.</i>

71
00:14:54,105 --> 00:14:56,460
<i>To think that Havana was
"The Paris of the Caribbean."</i>

72
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:05,468
<i>Thaùs what tourists and whores
called her.</i>

73
00:15:06,997 --> 00:15:08,794
<i>A Tegucigalpa of the Caribbean...</i>

74
00:15:09,584 --> 00:15:12,462
<i>... thaùs what it looks like today.</i>

75
00:15:17,344 --> 00:15:19,255
<i>Not only because "El Encanto"
has gone...</i>

76
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:21,716
<i>...and the stores are half empty...</i>

77
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:24,056
<i>... but because of the people.</i>

78
00:15:51,013 --> 00:15:53,447
<i>What does life mean for them?</i>

79
00:15:54,810 --> 00:15:58,166
<i>And what does life mean for me?</i>

80
00:16:00,192 --> 00:16:01,830
<i>But I'm not like them.</i>

81
00:16:09,245 --> 00:16:13,124
They're making the first socialist
revolution in America. So what?

82
00:16:15,378 --> 00:16:19,451
They're going back to the jungle,
hungry, like the Haitians.

83
00:16:19,842 --> 00:16:22,037
They beat Napoleon, and so?

84
00:16:22,429 --> 00:16:26,900
The worlds most important sugar
industry, before the revolution.

85
00:16:27,311 --> 00:16:29,427
Now look what they've made of it.

86
00:16:30,106 --> 00:16:31,459
Times change.

87
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:33,936
Sergio, iùs not our own problem.

88
00:16:34,236 --> 00:16:37,865
Iùs between the Russians and the
Americans, nothing to do with us.

89
00:16:38,617 --> 00:16:42,405
I tell you this whole thing
will blow up, Sergio.

90
00:16:42,789 --> 00:16:46,577
Whichever of them throws the first
punch, we'll catch it.

91
00:16:46,961 --> 00:16:50,920
Why? Because we're a tiny,
little island.

92
00:16:52,176 --> 00:16:55,452
You'll catch the punch,
because I won't be here.

93
00:16:56,933 --> 00:17:00,482
<i>To think we've been friends
for over five years.</i>

94
00:17:03,233 --> 00:17:07,988
Under Batista things got to
breaking point for you.

95
00:17:08,406 --> 00:17:14,038
Not me, I kept out of politics,
I have a clear conscience.

96
00:17:15,290 --> 00:17:18,919
All I've ever done is work,
like an animal.

97
00:17:20,171 --> 00:17:24,847
Just think of Anita. So beautiful,
yet living on a diet of black beans.

98
00:17:25,261 --> 00:17:26,614
Iùs not good enough.

99
00:17:27,473 --> 00:17:32,388
Yet they have the know-how to
develop the country's economy.

100
00:17:35,024 --> 00:17:36,537
Yes, the know-how.

101
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:41,615
The Americans know how to
make things run properly.

102
00:17:50,837 --> 00:17:55,388
- Check the oil.
- I haven't any, but I can check it.

103
00:17:57,887 --> 00:17:59,400
Why bother?

104
00:18:07,775 --> 00:18:10,528
I've got to hand it in
just as it was.

105
00:18:12,323 --> 00:18:16,157
Iùs been inventoried. If iùs
not as it was, I can't leave.

106
00:18:28,469 --> 00:18:33,338
You'll have to touch it up with
synthetic paint somehow.

107
00:18:34,644 --> 00:18:38,523
You'll have to paint this part,
at least.

108
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:48,533
<i>He says a Cuban can stand
everything except hunger.</i>

109
00:18:48,996 --> 00:18:51,271
<i>Think how we've starved
since the Spaniards came.</i>

110
00:18:56,422 --> 00:18:58,094
<i>In Latin America...</i>

111
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:01,698
<i>... four children die of malnutrition
every minute.</i>

112
00:19:02,389 --> 00:19:05,904
<i>In ten years twenty million
children will have died.</i>

113
00:19:06,978 --> 00:19:10,857
<i>Equal to the death roll of
the Second World War.</i>

114
00:19:24,459 --> 00:19:26,051
A symbol of decadence.

115
00:19:26,378 --> 00:19:30,132
If I keep it here I don't have to
get it repaired.

116
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:32,142
Well, if you prefer walking...

117
00:19:32,428 --> 00:19:36,546
No, but I feel happier.
Iùs a way out of problems.

118
00:19:39,395 --> 00:19:42,831
They say the latest American cars
are incredible.

119
00:19:43,234 --> 00:19:45,828
I was reading a magazine
Julio lent me.

120
00:19:46,363 --> 00:19:50,959
Sealed engines, two spark plugs,
a two year guarantee.

121
00:19:51,411 --> 00:19:55,165
If it breaks down they give you
another one.

122
00:19:55,583 --> 00:19:58,256
Thaùt's the only answer to
our mechanics.

123
00:19:58,712 --> 00:20:00,384
<i>People are becoming more stupid.</i>

124
00:20:00,798 --> 00:20:05,474
- Pablo's right: The French stink.
- They're just naturally dirty.

125
00:20:06,681 --> 00:20:10,469
I don't care if they confiscate
the lot.

126
00:20:11,396 --> 00:20:14,354
Iùs all the same to me.

127
00:20:14,817 --> 00:20:18,332
But I'm not staying safe indoors,
like when they fought Batista.

128
00:20:19,990 --> 00:20:22,709
Truth is, I never thought
they'd topple him.

129
00:20:24,246 --> 00:20:29,957
I must do something now, or I'll be
lost when this thing blows over.

130
00:20:31,380 --> 00:20:35,009
That'ùs what the Bay of Pigs
prisoners said.

131
00:20:38,473 --> 00:20:42,671
THE TRUTH OF THE GROUP
IS IN THE MURDERER

132
00:20:49,195 --> 00:20:53,507
<i>We found, in the invaders' military
organization, a social structure...</i>

133
00:20:53,993 --> 00:20:59,750
<i>... reflecting the social structure
and morality of the bourgeoisie.</i>

134
00:21:00,668 --> 00:21:02,386
<i>The priest.</i>

135
00:21:02,838 --> 00:21:04,715
<i>The free enterprise man.</i>

136
00:21:05,007 --> 00:21:07,043
<i>The dilettante official.</i>

137
00:21:07,970 --> 00:21:09,528
<i>The torturer.</i>

138
00:21:10,681 --> 00:21:12,273
<i>The philosopher.</i>

139
00:21:13,352 --> 00:21:14,705
<i>The politician.</i>

140
00:21:16,314 --> 00:21:18,669
<i>And many sons of good families.</i>

141
00:21:21,863 --> 00:21:24,502
<i>Each of them had specific duties...</i>

142
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:27,020
<i>... yet it was the whole, the group...</i>

143
00:21:27,370 --> 00:21:29,679
<i>... which gave meaning to
