144
00:21:32,543 --> 00:21:36,536
<i>CalviÒo was a murderer who even
horrified the bourgeoisie.</i>

145
00:21:37,383 --> 00:21:41,217
The housecoat I wore
is still bloodstained.

146
00:21:42,056 --> 00:21:44,092
He kicked my stomach and I bled.

147
00:21:45,519 --> 00:21:49,876
But that wasn't enough for him.
Because I struggled...

148
00:21:50,484 --> 00:21:53,681
...they broke two of my vertebrae.

149
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:57,078
<i>They hit him with sticks.</i>

150
00:21:57,493 --> 00:21:59,882
<i>You hit him, too. He fell
on his knees...</i>

151
00:22:00,330 --> 00:22:01,922
<i>... you kicked him in the side.</i>

152
00:22:02,291 --> 00:22:05,124
<i>Then he fell down. Do you remember?</i>

153
00:22:05,587 --> 00:22:08,260
<i>You abused him even after
he was dead.</i>

154
00:22:14,849 --> 00:22:18,524
<i>You shot him, then laughed
at the way he died.</i>

155
00:22:20,147 --> 00:22:22,058
<i>On October 6th, at 7 PM...</i>

156
00:22:24,403 --> 00:22:26,121
<i>Do you deny it?</i>

157
00:22:28,617 --> 00:22:30,335
<i>Do you deny...</i>

158
00:22:30,703 --> 00:22:33,376
<i>...nine days after you had
killed Morua...</i>

159
00:22:33,832 --> 00:22:35,185
<i>... you boasted about it?</i>

160
00:22:37,337 --> 00:22:39,532
<i>- Do you deny it?
- I can't answer</i>

161
00:22:43,136 --> 00:22:46,094
<i>In all capitalist societies...</i>

162
00:22:46,557 --> 00:22:50,436
<i>... the same type of man is at
the disposal of the bourgeoisie.</i>

163
00:22:52,523 --> 00:22:55,083
<i>In the moral division of work...</i>

164
00:22:55,485 --> 00:22:57,760
<i>... the murderer enables others
to exist...</i>

165
00:22:58,197 --> 00:23:01,553
<i>... others not in direct contact
with death...</i>

166
00:23:02,036 --> 00:23:05,233
<i>... who, as individuals, wish to
keep their souls clean.</i>

167
00:23:10,004 --> 00:23:12,882
<i>Speaking for myself and
those like me...</i>

168
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,495
<i>... maybe a minority...</i>

169
00:23:15,845 --> 00:23:21,044
<i>... we're not like Ventura, or those
other miserable creatures.</i>

170
00:23:21,478 --> 00:23:27,110
<i>I didn't even know CalviÒo then.
I lived my own life.</i>

171
00:23:28,362 --> 00:23:32,958
<i>They're like disjointed elements of
a whole which no one fully admits.</i>

172
00:23:33,827 --> 00:23:37,786
<i>I can't answer for the others.
Everyone answers for himself.</i>

173
00:23:38,166 --> 00:23:41,203
<i>It seems that you want to accuse me...</i>

174
00:23:41,546 --> 00:23:45,505
<i>... of being the instigator of
the invasion.</i>

175
00:23:46,969 --> 00:23:49,802
<i>I insist my mission was
purely spiritual.</i>

176
00:23:50,224 --> 00:23:54,183
<i>I have never handled a weapon.</i>

177
00:23:55,814 --> 00:23:59,250
<i>Being mixed up in a conspiracy
doesn't make one a conspirator.</i>

178
00:23:59,778 --> 00:24:04,329
<i>As I've told you, I've always
taken a neutral stand.</i>

179
00:24:05,452 --> 00:24:09,650
<i>I'm apolitical; never had anything
to do with a political party.</i>

180
00:24:10,083 --> 00:24:14,998
<i>One's personal behaviour excuses
one from general responsibility.</i>

181
00:24:15,715 --> 00:24:20,584
<i>Everyone concentrates on himself
to escape contamination by others.</i>

182
00:24:21,389 --> 00:24:24,745
<i>Or else, by sinking into the group
to mask his own responsibility...</i>

183
00:24:25,186 --> 00:24:27,381
<i>... he divides his guilt with others.</i>

184
00:24:27,689 --> 00:24:30,408
<i>I wasn't the only one in the group.</i>

185
00:24:30,860 --> 00:24:34,296
<i>Conversely, the group may be
disowned...</i>

186
00:24:34,657 --> 00:24:37,091
<i>... when its members wish to
avoid responsibility.</i>

187
00:24:39,288 --> 00:24:42,360
<i>You're talking about the group's
idea, not mine.</i>

188
00:24:44,837 --> 00:24:48,193
<i>But the idea of group
responsibility...</i>

189
00:24:48,675 --> 00:24:53,112
<i>... is the murderer-torturer's
haven, his claim to moral innocence.</i>

190
00:24:53,515 --> 00:24:57,827
<i>Listen, I've committed no
direct crime, I tell you.</i>

191
00:24:58,229 --> 00:25:01,266
<i>But none of the cases considered...</i>

192
00:25:01,817 --> 00:25:04,968
<i>... shows the dialectic relationship
between individual and group.</i>

193
00:25:05,322 --> 00:25:07,711
<i>None of those who came with
CalviÒo...</i>

194
00:25:08,034 --> 00:25:11,583
<i>... see that they're part of a system
which entangles them in their acts.</i>

195
00:25:13,249 --> 00:25:15,160
<i>In the accounts of landowner
Freyre...</i>

196
00:25:17,379 --> 00:25:18,892
<i>... in the extreme unctions of
Lugo...</i>

197
00:25:19,757 --> 00:25:22,988
<i>... in the reasonings of
philosopher Andreu...</i>

198
00:25:23,429 --> 00:25:25,818
<i>... in the dismissals of
dilettante Rivero...</i>

199
00:25:26,391 --> 00:25:28,666
<i>... in Varona's "representative
democracy"...</i>

200
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:33,149
<i>... who could divine the death
